  "They are the dependent variables measured at the end of the test": "",
  "They are experimental errors that should have been eliminated first": "",
  "The soil, pots, water amount, and temperature are constants (controlled variables). Keeping them the same ensures that any differences in plant growth are due to the light level (independent variable), not other factors.": "",
  "A teacher asks students to test whether salt water freezes at a different temperature than fresh water. A student puts salt water in a large container and fresh water in a small container. What is the problem?": "",
